
╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║         Welcome to Tesla — NVIDIA DGX-1 GPU Cluster          ║
╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
║                                                              ║
║  Hardware : 8x NVIDIA Tesla V100-SXM2-32GB                   ║
║  Fabric   : NVLink hybrid cube-mesh (48 links @ 25.78 GB/s)  ║
║  CPUs     : 2 sockets × 20 cores × 2 threads = 80 logical    ║
║  NUMA     : GPUs 0-3 → NUMA 0 │ GPUs 4-7 → NUMA 1            ║
║  Scheduler: SLURM {{ slurm_version }} + slurmdbd                       ║
║                                                              ║
║  POLICIES                                                    ║
║  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────   ║
║  • Tiered access: gpu1 / gpu2 / gpu3 / gpu4 / deadline       ║
║  • Run 'tesla-tier' to see your tier & per-job limits        ║
║  • Storage: /home is 200GB SSD; /storage/nas/$USER unlimited ║
║  • GPU access ONLY through SLURM job allocations             ║
║                                                              ║
║  QUICK START                                                 ║
║  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────   ║
║  Submit a job  :  sbatch myjob.sh                            ║
║  Check queue   :  squeue -u $USER     (or:  tq)              ║
║  Cluster view  :  tesla-status                               ║
║  Cancel a job  :  scancel <JOBID>                            ║
║  Your tier     :  tesla-tier                                 ║
║                                                              ║
║  Sample batch script at: /etc/slurm/example_job.sh           ║
║                                                              ║
║  TIP: For multi-GPU jobs, keep GPUs within one NUMA node     ║
║       (0-3 or 4-7) to use NVLink instead of QPI.             ║
║                                                              ║
